<br>
If you enjoy being an organizer, then the class can be a lot of fun.  You decide when to pull, when to evac, whose turn it is to loot what.  You keep tabs on the health of everyone, of course, but you also track the mezzed mobs and their aggro (tossing in a stun or Atone to protect the casters), and which tank is getting the most aggro (and perhaps gently correcting the monks or rangers on how much they are getting).  In some situations, you are a damage dealer (rare, but it happens), the rooter, stunner, or... stranger things.<br>
<br>
And of course, if you are chatty and into role-playing, the cleric offers a lot of opportunity to do so, since you tend to have more typing time than the other classes, even in a no-down-time situation.<br>
<br>
Finally, there is the whole &quot;helping people&quot; thing, which appeals to many.  The warrior or enchanter may get the glory in battle, but ask any high-level character to name their favorite person on the server and it'll be a cleric, simply because they remember that tense hour-long CR where the cleric saved them three day's worth of experience.<br>
<br>
As for mercenary clerics?  Well, we dwarves tend to think of it as business expenses.  As in &quot;I'm just a simple business man.  I will do for you this favor. Some day, and that day may never come, I will call upon you to do a service for me....&quot;<br>
